<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.001 B 64/16.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Honduras</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Government and people of Honduras join me in thanking Your Excellency
                            and the Government and people of the United States for their very
                            sincere expressions of sorrow for the death of President General
                            Bonilla. Will Your Excellency accept our gratitude.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Francisco Bertrand</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>